{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-21T17:14:41.659Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Derivatives"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are the fundamental concept in calculus that measure "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "instantaneous rates of change"}, {"type": "text", "text": "—how quickly a function's output changes when you slightly perturb its input. They power neural network training through "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "gradients"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (vectors of derivatives) and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "backpropagation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (chain rule application), making them the engine of all optimization in Generative AI."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Derivatives — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is — Clear definition and intuition"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mathematical definition:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "derivative"}, {"type": "text", "text": " of function "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "f(x)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " at point "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "x"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "f'(x) = lim(h→0) [f(x+h) - f(x)] / h"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In simpler terms: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "slope of the tangent line"}, {"type": "text", "text": " at a point on the curve. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "link", "attrs": {"href": "http://d2l.ai/chapter_preliminaries/calculus.html", "target": "_blank", "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow", "class": "text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400", "title": null}}], "text": "d2l"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Geometric interpretation:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Imagine a curve y = f(x):\n\n     |\n     |      /\n  y  |     /  ← Tangent line (slope = f'(x))\n     |    /   ← Curve\n     |   /\n     |__/________\n        x\n\nDerivative f'(x) = slope at point x"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Derivative tells you \"if I nudge x by a tiny amount, how much does f(x) change?\""}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why it matters — Importance in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Derivatives are the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "engine of machine learning optimization"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "AI Application"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How derivatives apply"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient Descent"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Update weights: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "w = w - learning_rate × gradient"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Backpropagation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Chain rule computes gradients through neural network layers"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Loss Minimization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Derivatives show direction to reduce error"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Parameter Sensitivity"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradient shows which parameters matter most"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Optimization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Find minima/maxima by setting derivative = 0"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Real example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": In training a GPT model, derivatives compute how much each weight (millions of them) affects the loss, enabling gradient descent to update them."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefits — Key advantages"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Optimization"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Find minima/maxima of functions"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sensitivity analysis"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Quantify parameter importance"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Direction finding"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Gradient points to steepest ascent/descent"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Efficient learning"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Backpropagation computes all gradients in one pass"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Convergence"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Derivatives tell us when we've reached optimal solution"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-offs — Downsides and limitations"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-off"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Impact"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Computational cost"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Computing gradients for millions of parameters is expensive"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Local minima"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradient descent can get stuck in suboptimal solutions"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Numerical instability"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Derivatives can explode (gradient explosion) or vanish (gradient vanishing)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Non-differentiable functions"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Some operations (e.g., max) have undefined derivatives"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How it works — Deep dive into each concept"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. Derivatives (Single Variable)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Basic derivative rules"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Rule"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Formula"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Power Rule"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "d/dx(xⁿ) = nxⁿ⁻¹"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "d/dx(x³) = 3x²"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Constant Rule"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "d/dx(c) = 0"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "d/dx(5) = 0"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sum Rule"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "d/dx(f + g) = f' + g'"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "d/dx(x² + x) = 2x + 1"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Product Rule"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "d/dx(f·g) = f'g + fg'"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "d/dx(x·x²) = 1·x² + x·2x = 3x²"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Quotient Rule"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "d/dx(f/g) = (f'g - fg')/g²"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "d/dx(x/x²) = (1·x² - x·2x)/x⁴ = -1/x²"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Chain Rule"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "d/dx(f(g(x))) = f'(g(x))·g'(x)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "d/dx(sin(x²)) = cos(x²)·2x"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Common derivatives"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Function"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Derivative"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "x"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "1"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "x²"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "2x"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "x³"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "3x²"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "sin(x)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "cos(x)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "cos(x)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "-sin(x)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "eˣ"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "eˣ"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "ln(x)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "1/x"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. Partial Derivatives (Multi Variable)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Definition"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Derivative with respect to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "one variable while holding others constant"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "∂f/∂x = derivative of f(x,y) with y held constant"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "f(x, y) = x² + xy + y³\n\n# Partial derivative w.r.t. x (treat y as constant)\n∂f/∂x = 2x + y\n\n# Partial derivative w.r.t. y (treat x as constant)\n∂f/∂y = x + 3y²"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Python (SymPy)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import sympy as sp\n\nx, y = sp.symbols('x y')\nf = x**2 + x*y + y**3\n\n# Partial derivatives\ndf_dx = sp.diff(f, x)  # 2*x + y\ndf_dy = sp.diff(f, y)  # x + 3*y**2"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. Gradients (Vector of Partial Derivatives)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Definition"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Vector containing all partial derivatives:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "∇f = (∂f/∂x, ∂f/∂y, ∂f/∂z, ...)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Geometric meaning"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Points in direction of "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "steepest ascent"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "f(x, y) = x² + xy + y³\n\n# Gradient\n∇f = (∂f/∂x, ∂f/∂y) = (2x + y, x + 3y²)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "At point (1, 2):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "∇f(1, 2) = (2×1 + 2, 1 + 3×2²) = (4, 13)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Python"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\ndef f(x, y):\n    return x**2 + x*y + y**3\n\n# Gradient at point (1, 2)\ngradient = np.array([4, 13])"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. Chain Rule (For Composed Functions)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Single variable"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "d/dx[f(g(x))] = f'(g(x)) · g'(x)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "f(x) = sin(x²)\n\n# Chain rule:\n# Outer: sin(u) → derivative = cos(u)\n# Inner: u = x² → derivative = 2x\nf'(x) = cos(x²) · 2x"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Multi-variable (Backpropagation)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[downstream gradient] = [upstream gradient] × [local gradient]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Neural network example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loss L = f(g(h(x)))\n\n∂L/∂x = ∂L/∂f · ∂f/∂g · ∂g/∂h · ∂h/∂x  (chain rule)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How to implement — Practical examples"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example 1: Computing derivatives with NumPy/Autograd"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\n# Function: f(x) = x²\ndef f(x):\n    return x**2\n\n# Derivative at x = 3 (numerical approximation)\nh = 1e-5\nderivative = (f(3 + h) - f(3)) / h\nprint(f\"f'(3) ≈ {derivative}\")  # ≈ 6 (exact: 2x = 6)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example 2: Computing gradients with PyTorch"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\n\n# Create tensor with gradient tracking\nx = torch.tensor([1.0, 2.0, 3.0], requires_grad=True)\n\n# Function: f(x) = x₁² + x₂·x₃\ny = x[0]**2 + x [medium](https://medium.com/@danailkhan1999/calculus-in-data-science-how-derivatives-power-optimization-algorithms-37ba6ab616ff)*x [web.stanford](https://web.stanford.edu/class/archive/cs/cs224n/cs224n.1214/slides/cs224n-2021-lecture03-neuralnets.pdf)\n\n# Compute gradients\ny.backward()\n\nprint(f\"Gradient: {x.grad}\")  # [2, 3, 2]\n# ∂f/∂x₁ = 2x₁ = 2\n# ∂f/∂x₂ = x₃ = 3\n# ∂f/∂x₃ = x₂ = 2"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example 3: Gradient Descent"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\n# Function to minimize: f(x) = x²\ndef f(x):\n    return x**2\n\n# Derivative: f'(x) = 2x\ndef derivative(x):\n    return 2*x\n\n# Gradient descent\nx = 5.0  # Start at x = 5\nlearning_rate = 0.1\nnum_iterations = 100\n\nfor i in range(num_iterations):\n    gradient = derivative(x)\n    x = x - learning_rate * gradient  # Update rule\n    \n    if i % 20 == 0:\n        print(f\"Iteration {i}: x = {x:.4f}, f(x) = {f(x):.4f}\")\n\nprint(f\"Final: x = {x:.6f}, f(x) = {f(x):.6f}\")  # x ≈ 0, f(x) ≈ 0"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Updates"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "x = 5.0 → x = 5.0 - 0.1×10 = 4.0\nx = 4.0 → x = 4.0 - 0.1×8 = 3.2\nx = 3.2 → x = 3.2 - 0.1×6.4 = 2.56\n...\nx → 0 (minimum)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example 4: Backpropagation in Neural Network"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\nimport torch.nn as nn\n\n# Simple neural network\nclass SimpleNN(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.layer1 = nn.Linear(3, 2)\n        self.layer2 = nn.Linear(2, 1)\n    \n    def forward(self, x):\n        x = torch.relu(self.layer1(x))\n        x = self.layer2(x)\n        return x\n\n# Create model\nmodel = SimpleNN()\n\n# Input and target\nx = torch.tensor([[1.0, 2.0, 3.0]])\ny_true = torch.tensor([[5.0]])\n\n# Forward pass\ny_pred = model(x)\n\n# Loss (MSE)\nloss = ((y_pred - y_true)**2).mean()\n\n# Backward pass (chain rule applies automatically)\nloss.backward()\n\n# Gradients computed via chain rule\nprint(f\"Layer 1 weight gradient: {model.layer1.weight.grad.shape}\")\nprint(f\"Layer 2 weight gradient: {model.layer2.weight.grad.shape}\")"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Chain rule flow"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loss → layer2 → layer1 → input\n  ∂L/∂w₂ = ∂L/∂y_pred × ∂y_pred/∂w₂\n  ∂L/∂w₁ = ∂L/∂y_pred × ∂y_pred/∂layer2 × ∂layer2/∂layer1 × ∂layer1/∂w₁"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example 5: Partial derivatives for multi-parameter function"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\n# Loss function: L(w1, w2, w3) = w₁² + 2w₂² + 3w₃²\ndef loss(w1, w2, w3):\n    return w1**2 + 2*w2**2 + 3*w3**2\n\n# Partial derivatives\ndef grad_w1(w1, w2, w3):\n    return 2*w1  # ∂L/∂w₁\n\ndef grad_w2(w1, w2, w3):\n    return 4*w2  # ∂L/∂w₂\n\ndef grad_w3(w1, w2, w3):\n    return 6*w3  # ∂L/∂w₃\n\n# Gradient vector\ngradient = np.array([grad_w1(1, 2, 3),\n                     grad_w2(1, 2, 3),\n                     grad_w3(1, 2, 3)])\n# = [2, 8, 18]\n\nprint(f\"Gradient: {gradient}\")"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common mistakes — Pitfalls to avoid"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mistake"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Correction"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Confusing derivative with gradient"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Derivative = single value (1D); Gradient = vector (multi-D)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Not using autograd"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use PyTorch/TensorFlow autograd instead of manual derivatives"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Ignoring chain rule"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Always apply chain rule for composed functions (backpropagation)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Fixed learning rate"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use adaptive learning rates (Adam, RMSprop)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient explosion"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Clip gradients: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "gradient = min(gradient, 5.0)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient vanishing"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use ReLU, batch normalization to prevent vanishing gradients"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best practices — Proven approaches"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. Use autograd frameworks"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\n\n# PyTorch automatically computes gradients\nx = torch.tensor([1.0, 2.0], requires_grad=True)\ny = x**2 + 3*x\ny.backward()\nprint(x.grad)  # [5, 7]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. Clip gradients to prevent explosion"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Gradient clipping\ntorch.nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(model.parameters(), max_norm=1.0)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. Use adaptive optimizers"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch.optim as optim\n\noptimizer = optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=0.001)  # Adaptive learning rate"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. Check gradient magnitude"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "for param in model.parameters():\n    if param.grad is not None:\n        print(f\"Gradient magnitude: {param.grad.norm()}\")"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Derivative = rate of change"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "f'(x) = lim(h→0) [f(x+h) - f(x)] / h"}, {"type": "text", "text": " "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "link", "attrs": {"href": "http://d2l.ai/chapter_preliminaries/calculus.html", "target": "_blank", "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow", "class": "text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400", "title": null}}], "text": "d2l"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Partial derivative"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Derivative w.r.t. ONE variable, holding others constant"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient = vector of partials"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "∇f = (∂f/∂x, ∂f/∂y,...)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " points to steepest ascent "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "link", "attrs": {"href": "http://d2l.ai/chapter_preliminaries/calculus.html", "target": "_blank", "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow", "class": "text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400", "title": null}}], "text": "d2l"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Chain rule"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "d/dx[f(g(x))] = f'(g(x)) · g'(x)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Backpropagation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Chain rule applied recursively through neural network layers"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient descent"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "w = w - learning_rate × gradient"}, {"type": "text", "text": " minimizes loss"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Use autograd"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": PyTorch/TensorFlow compute gradients automatically"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient clipping"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Prevent exploding gradients"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adaptive optimizers"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Adam, RMSprop adjust learning rates automatically"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For Generative AI, derivatives are the foundation: every weight update in training, every backpropagation step, and every optimization algorithm relies on computing derivatives to minimize loss and improve model performance."}]}]}}